1
00:01:48,375 --> 00:01:52,055
I'm so sorry.
Can you help me? My tire...

2
00:01:52,215 --> 00:01:55,415
Sorry. I have an appointment.
I don't like to be late.

3
00:01:55,695 --> 00:01:58,256
Well, would you rather be late or dead?

4
00:02:00,015 --> 00:02:03,735
- You don't want to do this.
- Step out of the car.

5
00:02:10,376 --> 00:02:12,455
Whoo! Let's go, fellas!

6
00:02:12,656 --> 00:02:15,536
Come on, baby! Yes!

7
00:02:15,736 --> 00:02:17,936
Take it easy. The car's brand-new.

8
00:02:18,136 --> 00:02:23,016
- No problem, buddy. I got this.
- Baby, let's ride. Time to go.

9
00:02:23,296 --> 00:02:24,953
- Your parents know the kind of
company you're keeping?

10
00:02:24,955 --> 00:02:25,903
- Shut up.

11
00:02:27,696 --> 00:02:29,616
- This shit ain't working.
- It's coded.

12
00:02:29,817 --> 00:02:31,737
- What's the code?
- I can't give you that.

13
00:02:31,937 --> 00:02:35,016
We'll have to beat it out of you.
Get out the car.

14
00:02:35,297 --> 00:02:38,177
Come on, man. What you got for me?

15
00:02:38,376 --> 00:02:41,057
Kick your ass!

16
00:02:41,537 --> 00:02:43,537
Hold on.

17
00:02:43,737 --> 00:02:46,897
It just came out of the dry cleaner's.

18
00:03:06,178 --> 00:03:09,818
Hands up.
Stop moving or I will shoot you.

19
00:03:10,018 --> 00:03:12,498
Don't you have homework to do?

20
00:03:14,418 --> 00:03:17,778
- Why don't you go and do it?
- OK. I'm sorry.

21
00:03:21,698 --> 00:03:23,819
Late.

22
00:04:29,821 --> 00:04:32,101
Hey! Hey!

23
00:04:33,061 --> 00:04:37,382
- The game, the game, the game!
- What's the first rule when entering a man's car?

24
00:04:37,661 --> 00:04:41,301
- Respect a man's car, a man respects you.
- Rule number two.

25
00:04:41,501 --> 00:04:45,422
- Greet the man. Good afternoon, Frank.
- Good afternoon, Jack.

26
00:04:45,742 --> 00:04:49,262
- Can we play the game?
- I should think you'd be tired after school.

27
00:04:49,582 --> 00:04:53,102
- You're afraid I'm gonna win.
- You'll be too worn out to do your homework.

28
00:04:53,302 --> 00:04:57,062
- It's Friday. I don't have any homework.
- In that case, the game.

29
00:04:57,342 --> 00:05:01,662
- Yes!
- But first, what's the third rule of the car?

30
00:05:01,942 --> 00:05:03,262
Good.

31
00:05:18,903 --> 00:05:23,423
Five points. I'm white,
I'm round, but I'm not always around.

32
00:05:23,703 --> 00:05:26,503
- A tennis ball?
- Tennis balls are yellow.

33
00:05:39,343 --> 00:05:40,984
Four points.

34
00:05:41,143 --> 00:05:44,824
Sometimes I'm half, sometimes I'm whole.
Sometimes a slice of me is all you know.

35
00:05:44,983 --> 00:05:47,104
- A loaf of bread?
- No.

36
00:05:52,304 --> 00:05:56,105
Three points. Sometimes I'm light,
sometimes I'm dark. Sometimes I'm both.

37
00:05:56,304 --> 00:05:58,145
- I know. A light bulb.
- No.

38
00:05:58,344 --> 00:06:00,545
- A pizza!
- No.

39
00:06:59,707 --> 00:07:02,386
Audrey. Audrey! Stop walking away from me.

40
00:07:02,667 --> 00:07:05,667
Listen, we've got to finish this conversation.

41
00:07:08,147 --> 00:07:09,987
Where's he going?

42
00:07:13,347 --> 00:07:15,627
OK, look at me. Last clue for all the points.

43
00:07:15,827 --> 00:07:20,027
Everyone wants to walk on me,
but only a happy few ever have.

44
00:07:20,348 --> 00:07:22,347
Take your time.

45
00:07:30,388 --> 00:07:33,188
- Hey, bud.
- Shh! Mom, it's the game. I'm trying to think.

46
00:07:33,468 --> 00:07:36,908
- Sorry. Hey, Frank. How are you today?
- Well, Mrs. Billings.

47
00:07:37,108 --> 00:07:40,468
- Can I team up with Mom?
- I don't know. It's not in the rules.

48
00:07:40,748 --> 00:07:44,109
Come on. What's the point in having rules
if you can't bend 'em?

49
00:07:44,308 --> 00:07:47,109
- OK. Just this once.
- Yeah!

50
00:07:47,388 --> 00:07:49,948
All right. Give me some clues.

51
00:07:50,148 --> 00:07:55,229
It's round, but not always around. It's light
sometimes, dark sometimes, or both.

52
00:07:55,509 --> 00:07:59,829
Everyone wants to walk on it,
but only a happy few ever have.

53
00:08:00,149 --> 00:08:03,469
- That is a hard one.
- Tell me about it.

54
00:08:06,669 --> 00:08:09,149
- The moon!
- Correct.

55
00:08:09,349 --> 00:08:11,429
Good job. All right. Come on.

56
00:08:11,629 --> 00:08:13,949
- See you Monday.
- Bye, Frank. Thanks.

57
00:08:14,149 --> 00:08:16,429
- Keep your snacks in the kitchen.
- Bye, Mom.

58
00:08:16,630 --> 00:08:19,510
He's really taken to you
in the month you've been with us.

59
00:08:19,710 --> 00:08:23,430
- Likewise.
- Too bad you can't stay on when Tony's back.

60
00:08:23,710 --> 00:08:26,790
It was just a favor.
I don't usually do this sort of a job.

61
00:08:27,070 --> 00:08:30,070
I thought you were a professional driver.

62
00:08:30,230 --> 00:08:32,150
A different kind of driving.

63
00:08:34,390 --> 00:08:38,310
Well, we're all gonna miss you
when you're gone.

64
00:08:44,831 --> 00:08:46,070
And...

65
00:08:46,271 --> 00:08:48,751
thank you for what you did.

66
00:08:48,950 --> 00:08:50,951
For what?

67
00:08:51,151 --> 00:08:55,191
For turning the car around so that
Jack wouldn't have to see us fighting.

68
00:08:55,471 --> 00:08:59,111
- You really know kids, don't you?
- I know fighting.

69
00:08:59,311 --> 00:09:01,711
He hasn't seen Jack in months,

70
00:09:01,911 --> 00:09:04,872
and when he gets back,
all I hear is what I'm doing wrong.

71
00:09:05,151 --> 00:09:10,431
You'd think that after being separated
for a year that he would...

72
00:09:11,792 --> 00:09:15,231
I'm sorry. You don't have to hear this.

73
00:09:15,432 --> 00:09:20,872
It's OK. For what it's worth,
I think you're doing a great job with Jack.

74
00:09:21,272 --> 00:09:22,512
Thank you.

75
00:09:22,632 --> 00:09:25,312
Any time I can be of help,
if there's anything you need.

76
00:09:25,472 --> 00:09:28,272
That's really sweet of you, Frank.

77
00:09:28,552 --> 00:09:31,153
I might have to take you up on it.

78
00:09:33,913 --> 00:09:39,033
I almost forgot. I'm supposed to take Jack to
the doctor tomorrow morning for a checkup,

79
00:09:39,313 --> 00:09:43,713
but I'm organizing a party for him, even
though his birthday's not until next week.

80
00:09:46,513 --> 00:09:51,753
So, while I decorate and his friends arrive,
I was thinking, if you wouldn't mind...

81
00:09:52,153 --> 00:09:55,113
- I'll take him.
- I feel funny cutting into your weekend.

82
00:09:55,313 --> 00:09:58,274
I'm just picking up a friend at the airport
later on in the day.

83
00:09:58,593 --> 00:10:00,794
- That's nice.
- What is?

84
00:10:00,993 --> 00:10:03,953
The guys on security
say you're a bit of a loner. Um...

85
00:10:04,154 --> 00:10:08,554
- So it's just nice to hear you have a friend.
- He's not really a friend.

86
00:10:08,834 --> 00:10:10,954
He's French.

87
00:10:11,153 --> 00:10:13,714
I'll call you back.

88
00:10:13,914 --> 00:10:16,914
Audrey. I'd like to finish our conversation.

89
00:10:21,994 --> 00:10:24,754
If anything comes up before then,
you have my cell.

90
00:10:24,954 --> 00:10:28,875
- Nothing will come up, Mrs. Billings.
- Audrey.

91
00:10:29,154 --> 00:10:30,515
Audrey.

92
00:10:59,476 --> 00:11:02,275
- Yeah, hello?
- Confirmed for tomorrow. 9am.

93
00:11:48,877 --> 00:11:52,518
Tomorrow, 9am. Only change -
the driver'll be taking him, not the mother.

94
00:11:52,718 --> 00:11:53,958
Even better.

95
00:12:00,078 --> 00:12:02,878
Vasily?

96
00:12:12,478 --> 00:12:15,038
- Is it stable?
- Yes, it's stable.

97
00:12:15,158 --> 00:12:17,359
And the antidote?

98
00:12:24,838 --> 00:12:26,359
See you tomorrow.

99
00:12:37,599 --> 00:12:40,959
The drug-enforcement ministers
of six Latin American countries

100
00:12:41,240 --> 00:12:43,239
arrived in Miami for a summit meeting...

101
00:12:43,439 --> 00:12:46,600
Yeah. Martin, Frank.
1156 Palmeadow.

102
00:12:46,799 --> 00:12:51,479
I'm waiting for an express delivery.
That's what you told me 45 minutes ago.

103
00:12:51,800 --> 00:12:55,440
I don't need anything else.
Just get me the pizza.

104
00:12:55,720 --> 00:12:58,200
- I'm not paying for that...
- Hi.

105
00:12:59,280 --> 00:13:00,400
Hi.

106
00:13:01,560 --> 00:13:05,800
So, it's one medium pie, no mozzarella,
extra olives and extra anchovies,

107
00:13:06,081 --> 00:13:08,200
which amounts to $11.95.

108
00:13:08,361 --> 00:13:10,881
- I hope you're hungry.
- You have no idea.

109
00:13:11,081 --> 00:13:14,121
I apologize for the delay, sir.

110
00:13:15,561 --> 00:13:17,481
Mrs. Billings.

111
00:13:19,321 --> 00:13:22,281
Audrey. Audrey.

112
00:13:23,041 --> 00:13:26,321
- What are you doing?
- What does it look like I'm doing?

113
00:13:26,521 --> 00:13:30,442
- Have you been drinking?
- A little.

114
00:13:32,362 --> 00:13:35,242
You said if I needed anything.

115
00:13:35,441 --> 00:13:39,241
- I can't.
- Why? Because of who I am?

116
00:13:40,522 --> 00:13:42,802
Because of who I am.

117
00:13:52,202 --> 00:13:55,842
I feel so lost. So confused.

118
00:13:57,203 --> 00:13:59,322
Who isn't?

119
00:14:08,882 --> 00:14:11,402
Thank you, Frank.

120
00:14:12,363 --> 00:14:14,923
For the time and...

121
00:14:15,123 --> 00:14:17,723
your respect.

122
00:14:17,923 --> 00:14:20,603
I think it's what I needed the most.

123
00:14:22,803 --> 00:14:24,523
Bye.

124
00:14:55,525 --> 00:14:58,285
- Am I gonna get a shot?
- I don't know.

125
00:15:20,165 --> 00:15:24,646
- Jeez. We're not open yet.
- I need to see the doctor immediately.

126
00:15:24,965 --> 00:15:28,966
Right. Dr. Koblin, if you'll come out here,
please. We have an issue.

127
00:15:29,285 --> 00:15:31,565
You'll have to state the medical problem.

128
00:15:31,766 --> 00:15:36,646
Actually, my problem's not medical.
It's psychological.

129
00:15:36,926 --> 00:15:39,326
Yes, Laura. What seems to be the problem?

130
00:15:39,526 --> 00:15:40,966
Me.

131
00:15:41,646 --> 00:15:43,926
I hate shots.

132
00:15:44,127 --> 00:15:47,686
Number one, there's no guarantee
you're getting a shot.

133
00:15:47,967 --> 00:15:51,726
There's no sense getting worked up
over something that might not happen.

134
00:15:57,846 --> 00:15:59,967
- Give me the news.
- Doctor said I'm cured.

135
00:16:00,807 --> 00:16:04,647
- Frank, it hurts a lot.
- I'd never let anyone hurt you a lot.

136
00:16:04,927 --> 00:16:07,647
- Promise?
- You know my fourth rule?

137
00:16:07,807 --> 00:16:11,767
Never make a promise
you can't keep. Come on.

138
00:16:13,847 --> 00:16:15,967
Close the door.

139
00:16:24,127 --> 00:16:25,368
Come on.

140
00:16:31,408 --> 00:16:34,288
- May I help you?
- Jack Billings to see Dr. Koblin.

141
00:16:34,488 --> 00:16:37,169
He's out sick today. He'll be seeing Dr. Tyberg.

142
00:16:37,448 --> 00:16:41,288
- I like Dr. Koblin.
- Don't worry. Dr. Tyberg's very nice.

143
00:16:41,489 --> 00:16:43,489
Just take him into room 3.

144
00:16:43,688 --> 00:16:45,329
- Where's Laura?
- Who?

145
00:16:45,529 --> 00:16:48,968
- You're standing at her desk.
- That Laura. She's out sick too.

146
00:16:49,249 --> 00:16:53,009
There's a lot of flu going around.
Now, come on. Doctor's got a busy day.

147
00:16:53,169 --> 00:16:56,169
Come on. It'll be over before you know it.

148
00:16:57,689 --> 00:16:59,529
Hey, hey!

149
00:17:00,289 --> 00:17:02,689
I'm Dr. Tyberg.

150
00:17:02,970 --> 00:17:04,890
Can't I wait for my doctor?

151
00:17:04,969 --> 00:17:07,969
Your doctor was called away
on an emergency.

152
00:17:08,250 --> 00:17:11,130
- The nurse said he had the flu.
- That was the emergency.

153
00:17:11,330 --> 00:17:17,370
He came down with flu, very quickly.
So, the sooner we start, the sooner we finish.

154
00:17:17,730 --> 00:17:20,890
Come. I show you something very cool.

155
00:17:21,090 --> 00:17:24,370
I'm sorry. Doctor-patient privacy in room.

156
00:17:24,650 --> 00:17:27,730
You can wait in reception area,
or glass of water, or...

157
00:17:27,890 --> 00:17:31,850
Hey, trust me. I am doctor.

158
00:17:32,131 --> 00:17:34,130
Please. It's phone.

159
00:17:37,291 --> 00:17:40,851
<i>- Yeah?
- Allô, allô.  Frank? I am here.</i>

160
00:17:41,131 --> 00:17:43,810
- You're early.
- Yeah, we had fantastic tailwinds.

161
00:17:44,011 --> 00:17:46,531
Put two hours on my vacation, just like that.

162
00:17:46,691 --> 00:17:50,251
From now on, it's the only way I'm flying.
Tailwinds or nothing.

163
00:17:50,531 --> 00:17:53,211
Glad you made it.

164
00:17:54,771 --> 00:17:59,571
Hello. Sorry, Dr. Dunietz is not in today.
Call back Monday.

165
00:18:05,132 --> 00:18:08,771
I'm a little tied up. You mind taking a cab?
You have the address, yes?

166
00:18:09,052 --> 00:18:14,612
Oh, thank you. I heard the fish down here
is fantastic. I could make us a bouillabaisse.

167
00:18:14,892 --> 00:18:17,412
You like bouillabaisse, Frank, no?

168
00:18:18,452 --> 00:18:20,652
I gotta go.

169
00:18:20,852 --> 00:18:21,892
Frank!

170
00:18:22,012 --> 00:18:24,492
Maybe we'll wait for his regular doctor.

171
00:18:24,693 --> 00:18:27,093
It's important that he receives immunizations.

172
00:18:27,372 --> 00:18:31,013
- I'm sure. But a week won't make a difference.
- No, we're doing it now.

173
00:18:52,493 --> 00:18:54,214
Get going, Jack!

174
00:20:02,136 --> 00:20:04,696
Look at me. Look at me.

175
00:20:04,896 --> 00:20:07,776
- Remember my promise?
- Yes.

176
00:20:27,737 --> 00:20:29,737
- It's... It's me!
- Get out!

177
00:20:34,057 --> 00:20:35,978
Frank.

178
00:21:04,378 --> 00:21:05,538
Shit.

179
00:21:14,139 --> 00:21:18,259
The patient's not cooperating.
Prep the vehicle.

180
00:21:31,300 --> 00:21:33,700
Come on, hurry.

181
00:21:37,380 --> 00:21:39,859
Don't worry. Everything's gonna be OK.

182
00:22:06,341 --> 00:22:10,061
- Freeze! Put your guns on the ground!
- Get down!

183
00:22:11,101 --> 00:22:13,621
<i>- Si.
- They got away.</i>

184
00:22:13,821 --> 00:22:15,421
<i>- Cazzo!
- Plan B?</i>

185
00:22:17,741 --> 00:22:18,701
Yes. Plan B.

186
00:22:37,022 --> 00:22:39,422
Oh, you made it.

187
00:22:39,622 --> 00:22:42,182
- Oh, what's that?
- Jack's birthday present.

188
00:22:42,382 --> 00:22:45,542
Baseball uniform, cleats, glove and a bat.

189
00:22:47,942 --> 00:22:51,583
- It's his favorite sport.
- It was. Last year.

190
00:22:51,782 --> 00:22:54,583
He's on a soccer team now. He's good.

191
00:22:54,862 --> 00:22:58,102
- You know, you should see him sometime.
- Hello.

192
00:22:58,303 --> 00:23:02,422
- Mr. And Mrs. Billings! They're coming!
- Hide, everyone. Hide!

193
00:23:09,703 --> 00:23:11,743
- Yes.
- Good morning, Mr. Driver.

194
00:23:11,943 --> 00:23:15,464
- Who is this?
- Look in your rear-view mirror and you'll see.

195
00:23:16,904 --> 00:23:19,424
I know what you're thinking.
Bulletproof glass.

196
00:23:19,503 --> 00:23:24,503
So tell me, in your experience - which judging
from the performance you put on in the office

197
00:23:24,784 --> 00:23:27,064
goes way beyond driving children to school -

198
00:23:27,383 --> 00:23:31,184
does bulletproof glass stop
a 7.62 armor-piercing round?

199
00:23:31,384 --> 00:23:34,664
Frank, why have you stopped the car?

200
00:23:37,424 --> 00:23:40,104
Don't look,
they are triangulated over 300 feet away.

201
00:23:40,304 --> 00:23:41,544
Frank, pick up.

202
00:23:41,745 --> 00:23:46,744
You screwed up my plan.
I am going to tell you how to set things right.

203
00:23:47,025 --> 00:23:50,465
Someone is going to appear in a few seconds.

204
00:24:01,705 --> 00:24:03,625
Let her in.

205
00:24:10,505 --> 00:24:13,025
Driver.

206
00:24:13,105 --> 00:24:16,266
Good boy. Good boy.

207
00:24:20,506 --> 00:24:21,666
Hi.

208
00:24:22,626 --> 00:24:24,546
Leave it on.

209
00:24:26,746 --> 00:24:31,146
Personally, I hate kids. I don't know
what your feelings are on the subject,

210
00:24:31,426 --> 00:24:36,626
but if you ever want to have any, make
no moves but the moves I tell you to make.

211
00:24:36,906 --> 00:24:41,426
You're in her hands now. They can be gentle
hands, but they can be the hands from hell.

212
00:24:41,706 --> 00:24:44,947
- Trust me on this one.
- Trust him on this one.

213
00:24:45,227 --> 00:24:47,066
Now, drive.

214
00:25:27,428 --> 00:25:29,348
Make a left.

215
00:25:29,548 --> 00:25:31,069
I said left.

216
00:25:51,429 --> 00:25:55,269
Listen, we keep doing this your way,
they're gonna catch us.

217
00:25:55,550 --> 00:25:58,229
- Do this my way, no one gets hurt.
- Where's the fun in that?

218
00:25:58,430 --> 00:26:00,909
Let's save the fun for later.

219
00:26:08,390 --> 00:26:09,470
Hey!

220
00:27:48,793 --> 00:27:49,874
Not bad.

221
00:27:50,073 --> 00:27:52,554
Didn't your mother
teach you to say thank you?

222
00:27:52,754 --> 00:27:54,674
She tried, and failed miserably.

223
00:27:54,834 --> 00:27:58,514
- I think we lost them.
- Think again.

224
00:28:02,914 --> 00:28:05,314
Thought complete. Let's go.

225
00:28:33,795 --> 00:28:38,675
You can't find him? He's one man in one car.
He's a chauffeur, for chrissakes.

226
00:28:38,955 --> 00:28:42,035
Not exactly, sir.
There's a possibility he was in on it.

227
00:28:42,315 --> 00:28:44,915
- That's impossible.
- How would you know?

228
00:28:45,116 --> 00:28:49,156
He could have been setting this up the
whole time, and you wouldn't have known.

229
00:28:49,436 --> 00:28:53,356
- And you are an expert on knowing people.
- His background.

230
00:28:54,516 --> 00:28:58,716
He's ex-Special Forces. Headed a commando
unit. Specialized in search and destroy.

231
00:28:58,996 --> 00:29:02,676
Been in and out of Lebanon, Syria, Sudan.
The man is a hunter.

232
00:29:02,956 --> 00:29:05,356
I don't care what his skills are
or where he's from.

233
00:29:05,556 --> 00:29:08,397
This is not a war zone,
this is an American city!

234
00:29:08,596 --> 00:29:10,716
Where's my son?

235
00:29:37,678 --> 00:29:39,958
