296
00:35:09,490 --> 00:35:12,770
Oh, the beach. The famous Miami Beach.

297
00:35:13,050 --> 00:35:16,811
Oh, my dream.
I would love to go to the beach.

298
00:35:20,171 --> 00:35:21,770
Maybe not.

299
00:35:21,890 --> 00:35:25,250
- Freeze! Who the fuck are you?
- I'm the cook.

300
00:35:27,451 --> 00:35:30,611
Oh. This is a mistake. A terrible mistake.

301
00:35:32,731 --> 00:35:36,931
Why we can't all just get along, you know?

302
00:35:52,172 --> 00:35:56,132
- Hello.
- It's Frank. Pretend it's someone else.

303
00:35:58,532 --> 00:36:00,252
Hi, Susan.

304
00:36:00,812 --> 00:36:02,812
No, I'm just here at home.

305
00:36:03,012 --> 00:36:06,172
I didn't do it, Audrey.
She had a gun on Jack. I had no choice.

306
00:36:06,372 --> 00:36:10,612
Yeah, I saw that. What do you know?

307
00:36:10,892 --> 00:36:13,573
- It's more than a kidnapping.
- They asked for a ransom.

308
00:36:13,772 --> 00:36:19,533
The doctors, they were fake. They were trying
to give Jack a shot. When I interrupted them...

309
00:36:21,532 --> 00:36:26,133
I promised Jack I wouldn't let anyone
hurt him. I'm not gonna break that promise.

310
00:36:26,413 --> 00:36:28,453
- Frank.
- I'll call you back.

311
00:36:31,493 --> 00:36:33,614
Audrey.

312
00:36:33,813 --> 00:36:39,573
- Is everything all right?
- That's a pretty stupid question to ask, Jeff.

313
00:36:45,974 --> 00:36:49,613
All right. So tell me again, Inspector Tarconi,

314
00:36:49,934 --> 00:36:55,214
why you didn't immediately
identify yourself as a police officer.

315
00:36:55,494 --> 00:37:00,574
Oh, I was overwhelmed
by the effectiveness of your operation,

316
00:37:00,934 --> 00:37:03,054
the sophistication of your equipment.

317
00:37:03,255 --> 00:37:08,535
You know, I work in a small office
in a small town. We only have small crimes.

318
00:37:08,814 --> 00:37:12,455
- I must admit I was a little insecure.
- You and Frank Martin are friends, right?

319
00:37:12,735 --> 00:37:18,295
A friend? Oh, I wouldn't say exactly a friend.
I know him, we have a relationship.

320
00:37:18,615 --> 00:37:20,535
A long relationship?

321
00:37:20,695 --> 00:37:23,295
- Not so long.
- But they found you cooking in his house.

322
00:37:23,495 --> 00:37:24,735
- I'm French!
- So?

323
00:37:24,935 --> 00:37:29,615
We don't need to know someone for long time in
order to cook for them. It's our way of breaking the ice.

324
00:37:29,896 --> 00:37:34,535
Take, for example, this sandwich
and coffee you so graciously offer me.

325
00:37:34,816 --> 00:37:37,855
Well, pardon me to think so,
but it's not very good.

326
00:37:38,056 --> 00:37:40,656
I know it sucks, but what's that
got to do with anything?

327
00:37:40,936 --> 00:37:42,016
Do you have a kitchen?

328
00:37:44,416 --> 00:37:46,296
Stay back. Stay back.

329
00:39:08,499 --> 00:39:11,179
Don't move. Smith!

330
00:39:11,299 --> 00:39:13,219
Drop it.

331
00:39:38,140 --> 00:39:40,620
Oh, Jesus. What happened?

332
00:39:40,821 --> 00:39:43,900
We'll take care of it for you.

333
00:39:49,740 --> 00:39:52,421
- Are you sure this safe?
- Look over your shoulder.

334
00:39:52,620 --> 00:39:55,020
We got you covered.

335
00:40:03,541 --> 00:40:10,061
As my mother used to say,
a meal is only limited by your imagination.

336
00:40:10,462 --> 00:40:12,862
<i>- Crème brûlée et croque monsieur.
- Cream brûlée?</i>

337
00:40:13,061 --> 00:40:14,221
- Crème brûlée.
- Cock?

338
00:40:14,381 --> 00:40:16,902
- Croque monsieur.
- Croque monsieur.

339
00:40:18,421 --> 00:40:20,262
<i>- Oui?
- Where are you?</i>

340
00:40:20,422 --> 00:40:23,502
- Cooking.
- Cooking. Can you talk?

341
00:40:23,702 --> 00:40:26,782
- Oh, speak of the devil. My mother.
- Mom.

342
00:40:26,942 --> 00:40:30,022
Please, do you mind?

343
00:40:30,302 --> 00:40:31,662
Thank you.

344
00:40:31,742 --> 00:40:33,662
<i>Oui, Maman. Je suis très bien arrivé. </i>

345
00:40:33,863 --> 00:40:37,622
<i>Oui, très très bien, merci. Oui.
Ah, oui, c'est une très jolie ville. </i>

346
00:40:37,902 --> 00:40:41,543
- May I ask who you're cooking for?
- For the US marshals.

347
00:40:41,822 --> 00:40:47,023
Once they found my badge, they were very
polite. They gave me a coffee and a sandwich.

348
00:40:47,303 --> 00:40:49,783
You wouldn't believe what passes
for food in this place, Frank.

349
00:40:49,982 --> 00:40:55,063
I am correcting the situation while they wait
for my chief to call back and confirm everything.

350
00:40:55,463 --> 00:40:59,943
Of course, that might take a while.
He's never there.

351
00:41:00,144 --> 00:41:03,303
- Anything about me?
- They are very interested about you.

352
00:41:03,504 --> 00:41:07,143
They want to know where you are.
Where are you?

353
00:41:07,423 --> 00:41:10,424
Nowhere for very long. Listen, hold on.

354
00:41:14,223 --> 00:41:16,944
Do you have access to a computer?

355
00:41:17,104 --> 00:41:20,584
Easier than having access
to something decent to eat.

356
00:41:35,265 --> 00:41:39,544
- Oh, handsome fellow. Who is he?
- That's what I need to know. Do they have an ID program?

357
00:41:39,745 --> 00:41:45,305
Forgive me. I'm not so used to this system.
Back home, there is one computer for ten of us.

358
00:41:45,705 --> 00:41:47,905
So, how is it with you, Frank?

359
00:41:48,105 --> 00:41:51,345
- It's a complicated story.
- Ah, you mean you are in the shit?

360
00:41:51,665 --> 00:41:55,385
- You might say that.
- In other words, your natural state.

361
00:41:55,586 --> 00:41:57,026
Voilà.

362
00:41:57,105 --> 00:42:03,346
A Russian biologist with advanced degrees from
the state laboratory for biological warfare in Siberia.

363
00:42:03,746 --> 00:42:09,106
- Do we have an address?
- Miami, Boca West, King Street, number 11.

364
00:43:48,350 --> 00:43:49,989
Get out!

365
00:44:15,031 --> 00:44:16,671
Hey!

366
00:44:20,191 --> 00:44:23,751
- What are you doing?
- Trying to catch a bus.

367
00:44:25,951 --> 00:44:27,671
Come on.

368
00:44:42,832 --> 00:44:47,152
What are you doing, driver?
Not so good on the water, hey?

369
00:44:50,512 --> 00:44:51,872
Stop it! Stop it!

370
00:45:21,673 --> 00:45:24,353
- OK. OK.
- Tell me about the doctor's office.

371
00:45:24,473 --> 00:45:27,713
- What doctor's office?
