465
00:56:12,831 --> 00:56:16,951
Once incubated, the virus becomes airborne,
so anyone he breathes on gets infected.

466
00:56:17,151 --> 00:56:19,831
Your son was a weapon.
The target is his father.

467
00:56:20,031 --> 00:56:24,711
- Jefferson? Well, why?
- Because of the conference. It's the only logical answer.

468
00:56:24,991 --> 00:56:27,991
Every drug-enforcement agency
in the hemisphere, in one room.

469
00:56:28,272 --> 00:56:31,152
Your husband breathes, the room dies.

470
00:56:36,872 --> 00:56:39,392
You gotta trust me, Audrey.

471
00:56:46,272 --> 00:56:48,592
Can you get to him?

472
00:56:48,872 --> 00:56:51,673
- What are you gonna do?
- Find the guy responsible.

473
00:56:51,872 --> 00:56:55,033
He has more of this.
For you and everybody else.

474
00:56:56,953 --> 00:56:59,152
For you now.

475
00:57:14,954 --> 00:57:15,914
We have a guest.

476
00:57:17,753 --> 00:57:20,834
- You're burning up.
- I'm OK.

477
00:57:20,993 --> 00:57:23,234
You gotta go. Go.

478
00:57:26,554 --> 00:57:27,833
Don't move!

479
00:58:11,075 --> 00:58:13,195
- Is the governor here?
- Everybody's gonna be here.

480
00:58:13,355 --> 00:58:16,435
The govenor, delegates
from all over the world.

481
00:58:16,555 --> 00:58:19,915
- Just a second. Hello.
- Jefferson, you can't go to the conference.

482
00:58:20,076 --> 00:58:23,236
- Is everything all right?
... to give him a deadly virus...

483
00:58:23,556 --> 00:58:26,516
- Audrey, I can't hear you. I'm inside.
- Now I've got it, and so do you.

484
00:58:26,716 --> 00:58:30,076
- Audrey, I can't hear you.
- Their plan is to infect everyone at the conference.

485
00:58:30,356 --> 00:58:33,036
- I'm gonna have to call you back.
- Jeff!

486
00:58:35,036 --> 00:58:38,117
Mr. Billings, are you all right?

487
00:58:38,316 --> 00:58:41,477
- I'm all right. Come on, let's go.
- You sure?

488
00:59:01,117 --> 00:59:04,117
<i>- Allô.
- You still a guest of the government?</i>

489
00:59:04,317 --> 00:59:09,078
They gave me the five-star accommodation.
Let me guess - you need my help.

490
00:59:09,477 --> 00:59:11,798
Are you near the computer?

491
00:59:11,958 --> 00:59:15,158
It's practically my pillow.
So, how do you want to start?

492
00:59:15,318 --> 00:59:21,478
- I don't know. I have nothing.
- Ah. My favorite type of investigation.

493
00:59:21,838 --> 00:59:24,638
<i>Let's see. Alors. </i>

494
00:59:25,318 --> 00:59:28,358
I'd like to take this opportunity
to introduce you to my delegates...

495
00:59:28,678 --> 00:59:32,959
Breathe. That's right,
breathe, my friend, breathe.

496
00:59:33,278 --> 00:59:36,319
Tomorrow, once these
bastards are out of the way

497
00:59:36,519 --> 00:59:41,239
and their co-operation agreements are dead and buried,
you know what the biggest problem is going to be?

498
00:59:41,518 --> 00:59:44,199
- What?
- Counting the money.

499
00:59:48,719 --> 00:59:51,199
- I can't wait for tomorrow.
- Ay-ay-ay!

500
00:59:55,439 --> 00:59:58,479
Aah. Gianni Chellini.

501
00:59:58,760 --> 01:00:03,280
Hires himself out to anyone looking to make
trouble like the Red Brigade, Shining Path.

502
01:00:05,399 --> 01:00:08,759
Someone accessed a database
on the 15th floor.

503
01:00:09,040 --> 01:00:12,880
That's Gonzalez. He's on vacation.

504
01:00:13,160 --> 01:00:17,680
Was behind the hostage-taking
of the OPEC ministers in Geneva.

505
01:00:17,960 --> 01:00:20,240
It was a nice piece of work.

506
01:00:24,561 --> 01:00:26,680
- Give me an address.
- Miami, East Highland,

507
01:00:26,880 --> 01:00:29,001
Pelican Drive, number 26900.

508
01:00:29,081 --> 01:00:31,961
- We've found the car.
- You're one great cop, Tarconi.

509
01:00:32,160 --> 01:00:35,880
Thank you for the compliment.
Now I'm going back to sleep.

510
01:00:39,241 --> 01:00:40,961
Hm. Maybe not.

511
01:00:43,281 --> 01:00:46,241
- Bumbaclaat, man! Move out the way!
- Move over.

512
01:00:46,441 --> 01:00:48,442
I'll do ya!

513
01:00:56,242 --> 01:00:58,162
Mommy.

514
01:00:59,281 --> 01:01:03,522
- Honey. You feeling better?
- A little bit.

515
01:01:03,802 --> 01:01:06,962
Why don't you try to go back to sleep, OK?

516
01:01:12,522 --> 01:01:14,723
Ma'am, are you all right?

517
01:01:24,523 --> 01:01:26,923
Jefferson. Jefferson, are you OK?

518
01:02:29,045 --> 01:02:31,165
OK, do it.

519
01:02:43,166 --> 01:02:47,006
- What are you doing?
- You know, last night got me thinking.

520
01:02:47,206 --> 01:02:49,606
How do we transport the antidote safely?

521
01:02:49,886 --> 01:02:53,126
We need something that won't break.
Something that can't be stolen.

522
01:02:53,326 --> 01:02:57,086
Something totally secure. Me.

523
01:03:02,926 --> 01:03:06,006
Impressive. Get dressed.

524
01:03:07,726 --> 01:03:08,687
Stop him.

525
01:03:11,727 --> 01:03:14,046
- These your friends?
- Not yet.

526
01:03:23,447 --> 01:03:25,927
- Where'd they go?
- The garage.

527
01:03:27,487 --> 01:03:29,207
- I'm out of ammo.
- Me too.

528
01:03:29,287 --> 01:03:31,327
- So am I.
- Where are the reloads?

529
01:03:31,487 --> 01:03:32,927
The garage.

530
01:03:34,288 --> 01:03:36,768
Check the house. Go, go, go!

531
01:03:40,608 --> 01:03:42,528
Get him! Get him!

532
01:05:31,547 --> 01:05:34,626
- What d'you want me to do?
- Keep the meter running.

533
01:05:34,907 --> 01:05:39,827
Bye. Don't worry, baby.
You're safe now. You're safe.

534
01:05:40,106 --> 01:05:43,826
You're so beautiful.
Remind me of my yellow poom-poom rider.

535
01:06:57,309 --> 01:06:59,110
Don't move.

536
01:06:59,230 --> 01:07:02,189
- Oh, Mr. Driver.
- I'll blow you into tomorrow.

537
01:07:02,390 --> 01:07:06,029
But then I'll bleed what you came for all over
the floor. You wouldn't want this, would you?

538
01:07:06,310 --> 01:07:09,750
Not after you worked so hard
trying to get to the antidote.

539
01:07:09,950 --> 01:07:12,350
Take a good look, Frank Martin.

540
01:07:12,550 --> 01:07:15,910
I'm a cure for what ails you.
I'm the only cure for what ails you.

541
01:07:16,191 --> 01:07:19,150
I am the antidote.

542
01:07:19,350 --> 01:07:22,431
But nice try. I'm impressed.
I didn't give you enough credit.

543
01:07:22,710 --> 01:07:26,550
- It took more than a driver to figure this out.
- I haven't figured it all out yet.

544
01:07:26,751 --> 01:07:29,910
Perhaps I can help you.
What part are you a little thick on?

545
01:07:30,191 --> 01:07:33,271
- You. Why?
- Oh.

546
01:07:33,471 --> 01:07:39,111
That's the easy part. It's a business deal, pure
and simple. I'm for hire to the highest bidder.

547
01:07:39,511 --> 01:07:42,751
In this case, the highest bidder
was the Colombian cocaine cartels

548
01:07:42,952 --> 01:07:46,111
that wanted these pesky lawmen
off their backs.

549
01:07:46,391 --> 01:07:49,552
You really think killing all these politicians
is going to make things easier for them?

550
01:07:49,751 --> 01:07:52,912
That's not my problem.
I was hired to do a job.

551
01:07:53,232 --> 01:07:57,511
I did the job, like you. Just my pay is better.

552
01:07:58,792 --> 01:08:01,352
My hair and my suit, too.

553
01:08:02,992 --> 01:08:05,312
Oh, Lola.

554
01:08:05,472 --> 01:08:08,752
Now, if you'll excuse me,
I have a plane to catch.

555
01:08:09,792 --> 01:08:12,032
Kill him.

556
01:08:12,192 --> 01:08:13,832
<i>Ciao, ciao. </i>

557
01:08:17,592 --> 01:08:19,873
- Don't even blink.
- What's in this for you?

558
01:08:20,072 --> 01:08:21,992
Pleasure...

559
01:08:24,392 --> 01:08:27,153
in killing you.

560
01:09:59,157 --> 01:10:01,636
We're coming to you live
from the Key Biscayne causeway

561
01:10:01,917 --> 01:10:05,757
where at least ten police cars are in
hot pursuit of a stolen red pick-up truck.

562
01:10:10,077 --> 01:10:13,037
Oh, my. This is just nuts.
Jim, are you getting that?

563
01:10:13,237 --> 01:10:17,637
There's another car that is swaying
past the police, as if they were standing still.

564
01:10:17,957 --> 01:10:21,477
- Son of a bitch can drive. Whoo.
- Yes, he can.

565
01:11:06,199 --> 01:11:08,279
We have clearance for takeoff.

566
01:11:08,399 --> 01:11:13,199
Sit back, enjoy your flight, and
we will be in Colombia before you know it.

567
01:11:55,761 --> 01:11:58,641
We have a problem with the landing gear.
I need to land.

568
01:11:58,720 --> 01:12:01,041
- Can we fly with the problem?
- Theoretically.

569
01:12:01,241 --> 01:12:04,761
Then you'll land when we get to Colombia.

570
01:12:05,081 --> 01:12:07,561
Go and see if you can lift it manually.

571
01:12:07,761 --> 01:12:11,001
Sorry for the inconvenience.
Nothing to worry about.

572
01:12:15,602 --> 01:12:18,401
Sorry, flight's been cancelled.

573
01:12:18,602 --> 01:12:21,962
I'm sorry to inform you
that you have been cancelled.

574
01:12:22,121 --> 01:12:25,001
Have a seat.

575
01:12:25,682 --> 01:12:28,202
Relax.

576
01:12:28,362 --> 01:12:31,242
Drink something.
Let's get to know each other.

577
01:12:31,362 --> 01:12:34,602
I think I know everything I need to know.

578
01:14:18,471 --> 01:14:20,391
Shit.

579
01:15:55,835 --> 01:16:00,035
Five points. What has eyes
but no ears, skin but no hair,

580
01:16:00,235 --> 01:16:02,035
it's white inside and brown outside?

581
01:16:02,236 --> 01:16:04,075
- Mom?
- A worm?

582
01:16:04,276 --> 01:16:07,715
- Wrong. Dad?
- A caterpillar.

583
01:16:07,996 --> 01:16:10,675
- Wrong.
- A potato.

584
01:16:14,596 --> 01:16:17,596
- May I help you?
- I was just leaving.

585
01:16:20,956 --> 01:16:22,876
- Coconut.
- Wrong.

586
01:16:23,036 --> 01:16:26,396
- A snake.
- Wrong.

587
01:16:26,716 --> 01:16:29,676
- A peanut.
- Yuck!

588
01:16:29,876 --> 01:16:31,956
- A hot dog.
- Wrong.

589
01:16:44,437 --> 01:16:46,557
- That was fast.
- Yeah.

590
01:16:47,797 --> 01:16:52,877
- Didn't want you to miss your plane.
- That's very thoughtful of you.

591
01:17:00,637 --> 01:17:02,838
Check it out, my man.

592
01:17:05,157 --> 01:17:08,798
You won't believe
what happened to me last night.

593
01:17:14,278 --> 01:17:17,518
I have something for you.
Since you never got to the beach.

594
01:17:17,838 --> 01:17:22,798
Oh, you know, water's water, sand is sand.
Here, there - it's all the same.

595
01:17:23,078 --> 01:17:25,118
Flight 069 to Paris.

596
01:17:25,318 --> 01:17:28,078
Thank you, Frank.
It was an interesting vacation.

597
01:17:28,279 --> 01:17:31,359
- What more could one ask for?
- Ah, yeah.

598
01:17:32,398 --> 01:17:35,959
<i>- Au revoir, Frank.
- Au revoir, my friend. Have a good flight.</i>

599
01:17:36,118 --> 01:17:38,439
I doubt it. They said it is all headwinds.

600
01:17:38,639 --> 01:17:42,279
I guess we can't have
everything we wish for, can we?

601
01:17:43,039 --> 01:17:45,239
No, we can't.

602
01:17:59,519 --> 01:18:00,680
Yeah.

603
01:18:00,880 --> 01:18:03,560
I'm looking for a transporter.

604
01:18:07,000 --> 01:18:08,640
I'm listening.

